LG Electronics has set aside Sh100 million for regional expansion targeting 10 retail outlets in East Africa. The company said the expansion has been informed by growing disposable income among the middle-class.&ldquo;We are thrilled to be rolling out more outlets in the region that will offer a first-class shopper experience to our clients,&rdquo; LG Eastern and Central Africa Moses Marji. The firm on Monday opened a new store at the Sarit Centre in Nairobi&rsquo;s Westalnds to kick off the expansion project. &ldquo;As a leading electronics company, we enjoy nothing more than contributing to the regions positive economic growth and delivering outstanding value to customers every day,&rdquo; Marji said.